Javascript important concept : 

Variables 
let a = 5 ;                // can be changed 
const name = "Payal"  // cannot be changed 
var c = "London"       // old way (avoid it)

Fucntions

1 Normal Function 
function abc(){
 console.log("hello");
}
abc();

2 Anonymous Function
fn without a name 
used inside other func (pass as arg like route or event handler)
used when we dont need to reuse the fn later 

function(){
 console.log("xyz");
}

()  =>{
 console.log("hi");
}
// call nai hota
// only pass

cant standalone or call directly 
hence assign to variable or use inside another function

const a = function(){
 console.log("xyz");
}
a();                      // works fine in JS

anonymmous func used as callback
Callback - a callback is just a fn as an arg to another function

setTimeOut(function(){
 console.log("Execute after 2 sec")
},2000);



app.get("/",function(req,res){res.send("Welcome")});
// express is called , then app is returned 
// endpoints /users /products

Destructing
it extract values from obj / array easily 

const user ={name:"Payal",age:23,city:"Kolkata"};
const

Array Destructuring 
const numbers =[10,20,30];
const [a,b]=numbers;
console.log(a);
console.log(b);

Arrow Functions
shorter syntax for functions
const add = (a,b) => a+b
console.log(add(2,3));

app.get("/user",(req,res) => {
 res.send("User Route");
});

Promises 
backend code need to wait for data like DB Queries or API's
getuserData(){
 
}

Async / Await
backend code need to wait for data like DB or API's
async function fetchdata(){
 try{}
 catch(err){
   console.error(err);
 }
}


